<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1370,1682]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
This species was previously referred to as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Weber)" baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[652,1034,1370,1395]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Soleidae" genus="Aseraggodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="klunzingeri">
<emphasis box="[652,933,1371,1395]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Aseraggodes klunzingeri</emphasis>
(Weber)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Allen, G. R." box="[1053,1185,1370,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref17973" refString="Allen, G. R. (1975) A preliminary checklist of the freshwater fishes of the Prince Regent River Reserve north-west Kimberley, Western Australia. In: Miles, J. M. &amp; Burbidge, A. A. (Eds), A biological survey of the Prince Regent River Reserve Northwest Kimberley, Western Australia in August, 1974. Wildlife Research Bulletin of Western Australia, 3, 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="1975">Allen 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Storey, A. W." box="[1201,1345,1370,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref19815" refString="Storey, A. W. (2003) Lower Ord River fish habitat survey. University of Western Australia report to Water and Rivers Commission. www. dsd. wa. gov. au / documents / Storey _ 2003 _ - _ Lower _ Ord _ River _ fish _ habitat _ survey. pdf" type="book" year="2003">Storey 2003</bibRefCitation>
), which according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall, J. E." box="[295,464,1406,1430]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="81 - 108" refId="ref19772" refString="Randall, J. E. (2007) Leptachirus, a new soleid fish genus from New Guinea and northern Australia, with descriptions of eight new species. Records of the Western Australia Museum, 24, 81 - 108." type="journal article" year="2007">Randall (2007)</bibRefCitation>
is actually a complex of several closely related species. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1090,1367,1406,1430]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Soleidae" genus="Aseraggodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="klunzingeri">
<emphasis box="[1090,1367,1406,1430]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Aseraggodes klunzingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="19" pageNumber="20" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
(now placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.E.Randall" authorityYear="2007" box="[402,536,1443,1467]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Soleidae" genus="Leptachirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[402,536,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Leptachirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), is confined to the Merauke region of 
<collectingRegion box="[976,1153,1442,1466]" country="Indonesia" name="Papua Barat" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Papua Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1165,1277,1442,1466]" name="Indonesia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, and the Kimberley species (also ranging to the Daly River, Northern Territory) is referrable to 
<taxonomicName box="[1080,1206,1479,1502]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Soleidae" genus="Leptachirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="triramus">
<emphasis box="[1080,1206,1479,1502]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">L. triramus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There are very few records of this species from the Kimberley; the few that exist suggest it is most commonly encountered within the Ord River system (
<figureCitation box="[369,452,1550,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="63.[151,250,1146,1169]" captionTargetBox="[262,1325,196,1122]" captionTargetId="figure-24@63.[257,1330,193,1125]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURE 51. Distribution of Leptachirus triramus in the Kimberley." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Randall, J. E." box="[477,635,1550,1574]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="81 - 108" refId="ref19772" refString="Randall, J. E. (2007) Leptachirus, a new soleid fish genus from New Guinea and northern Australia, with descriptions of eight new species. Records of the Western Australia Museum, 24, 81 - 108." type="journal article" year="2007">Randall 2007</bibRefCitation>
). There is also an additional record of what is most likely this species from Crystal Creek near the mouth of the Lawley River. Another specimen reported as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1168,1328,1587,1611]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Soleidae" genus="Aseraggodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="klunzingeri">
<emphasis box="[1168,1328,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. klunzingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Prince Regent River at the base of King Cascade by 
<bibRefCitation author="Allen, G. R." box="[755,900,1622,1646]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="89 - 96" refId="ref17973" refString="Allen, G. R. (1975) A preliminary checklist of the freshwater fishes of the Prince Regent River Reserve north-west Kimberley, Western Australia. In: Miles, J. M. &amp; Burbidge, A. A. (Eds), A biological survey of the Prince Regent River Reserve Northwest Kimberley, Western Australia in August, 1974. Wildlife Research Bulletin of Western Australia, 3, 89 - 96." type="journal article" year="1975">Allen (1975)</bibRefCitation>
is 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chabanaud" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[936,1176,1622,1646]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Soleidae" genus="Pardachirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rautheri">
<emphasis box="[936,1176,1622,1646]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Pardachirus rautheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. Morrison, Western Australian Museum, pers. com.).
</paragraph>
